The paper deals with the use of metric index structures for nearest neighbor queries, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The focus on incremental insertion and querying also suggests a potential fit with data structures (cs.DS). The use-case of malware analysis triage may also suggest a connection to computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the evaluation of different algorithms and metrics could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
